HEADWORD: Sulpharsenious
<hw>Sulph`ar*se"ni*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Of, pertaining to, or designating, a
hypothetical sulphacid (called also <xex>thioarsenious acid</xex>)
analogous to arsenious acid, and known only in its salts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sulpharsenite</ent>⟦br⟧
